

Created by ossfuzz folks 26 Feb 2026
I first found this on 14 May 2026!

oss fuzz 488137256
Direct-leak in _dwarf_internal_read_rnglists_header

testcase fuzz_die_cu-4889329913888768

Code in  _dwarf_elf_setup_all_section_groups()
  ( in dwarf_elf_load_headers.c)
had an incorrect response in looking for
SHF_GROUP records, and tried to treat
a non-group section as if it was a group-content-list
section. Chaos ensued, leading to a leaked record.

The object file here is very severly corrupted
and that contributed to the leakage:  we were
doing wrong things based on the following test.

-        if (!elf_sht_groupsec(psh->gh_type,name)) {
-            /* Step B */
-            if (elf_flagmatches(psh->gh_flags,SHF_GROUP)) {
-                ep->f_shf_group_flag_section_count++;
-            }
+        if (elf_sht_groupsec(psh->gh_type,name) ||
+            elf_flagmatches(psh->gh_flags,SHF_GROUP)) {
+            ep->f_shf_group_flag_section_count++;
+        } else {
             continue;
         }

This has been broken for a very long time,
it was definitely broken in the
libdwarf-20191104 release, so broken for at least
seven years. 2019 was the year support for Elf
GROUPs was added.
